- Yes, sir?

22:48.533 --> 22:50.350
- Where are you taking these?

22:50.350 --> 22:52.890
- Uh, she wanted me to
remove these until she can--

22:52.890 --> 22:55.470
- But I only took out one
bag out of my wardrobe.

22:55.470 --> 22:56.697
Where's the rest of them from?

22:56.697 --> 22:58.700
- Um, I have no idea.
- No!

22:58.700 --> 23:00.740
- I just know she had clothes upstairs,

23:00.740 --> 23:02.190
so she asked me to move them.

23:03.670 --> 23:06.363
- Lamont! Seriously?
- Mm-hmm.

23:08.490 --> 23:10.589
- Go get her for me, please.
- Yes, sir.

23:10.589 --> 23:11.589
- Holy shit.

23:13.924 --> 23:17.188
I mean. (laughs)

23:17.188 --> 23:18.300
- Ms. Karan?

23:18.300 --> 23:19.860
He say he want to talk to you.

23:19.860 --> 23:20.693
- Okay.

23:22.640 --> 23:23.620
- Ms. Karan.
- Yes?

23:23.620 --> 23:25.380
- Is this all yours?

23:25.380 --> 23:27.490
- That's what came from
out of the wardrobe.

23:27.490 --> 23:28.323
- Another wardrobe?

23:28.323 --> 23:30.370
- No, no, no, the one that you emptied.

23:30.370 --> 23:32.440
- No, I had one bag full of stuff.

23:32.440 --> 23:33.740
- No, this is the stuff

23:33.740 --> 23:36.083
that was in the black
wardrobe in your room.

23:37.940 --> 23:39.600
- But where's this stuff going now?

23:39.600 --> 23:41.460
- To his basement till I can sort it out.

23:41.460 --> 23:42.920
- His basement?
- Mm-hmm,

23:42.920 --> 23:44.950
'cause I don't have
anyplace to store here.

23:44.950 --> 23:45.783
- What is it?

23:45.783 --> 23:47.190
- It's my clothes.
- Clothes, her clothes.

23:47.190 --> 23:48.810
- The things that came
out of the black wardrobe

23:48.810 --> 23:50.920
that we keep locked up
in the Potomac Room.

23:50.920 --> 23:52.450
(Lamont laughing)

23:52.450 --> 23:53.400
- Do you ever ask yourself

23:53.400 --> 23:54.860
if you have a problem
holding on to things?

23:54.860 --> 23:57.103
Have you heard of the word hoarder?

23:58.130 --> 24:01.090
Ms. Karan, this is your business.

24:01.090 --> 24:03.790
This is your hotel, not your junk shop.

24:03.790 --> 24:04.623
- [Karan] Mm-hmm.

24:04.623 --> 24:05.670
- Can you get the team
out from the kitchen?

24:05.670 --> 24:07.160
I'd like to have a quick word
with you all on the terrace.

24:07.160 --> 24:07.993
- Yes, sir.

24:07.993 --> 24:08.865
- Um, good luck with that stuff.

24:08.865 --> 24:09.698
- Yes, sir.
- Yeah.

24:09.698 --> 24:10.531
- Thank you.

24:10.531 --> 24:12.310
- Ms. Karan, can we meet
the team on the terrace?

24:12.310 --> 24:15.360
One, two, three, four,
five, six, six bags.

24:15.360 --> 24:17.503
You want to check the
things for bugs as well.

24:24.270 --> 24:26.040
I'm in shock.

24:26.040 --> 24:26.873
Are you joining us, Ms. Sarah

24:26.873 --> 24:28.080
or are you still writing labels?

24:28.080 --> 24:29.157
- No, I'm not writing labels anymore.

24:29.157 --> 24:30.173
- No? Let's go.

24:31.410 --> 24:34.300
I arrive, the facade of the
outside looks beautiful.

24:34.300 --> 24:35.133
I walk through the door,

24:35.133 --> 24:37.650
and it's just like a cluster of shit.

24:37.650 --> 24:39.100
Crap everywhere.

24:39.100 --> 24:40.540
Mouldy bread in the reception.

24:40.540 --> 24:41.880
Freaky dolls.

24:41.880 --> 24:43.950
Up to the bedrooms that's,
like, just hideous.

24:43.950 --> 24:47.450
Wardrobe's packed with
clothes from 30 years ago.

24:47.450 --> 24:51.190
And I had to ask Ms. Karan
to get rid of the padlock

24:51.190 --> 24:54.780
so I can open up the wardrobe
and put my clothes in there.

24:54.780 --> 24:56.913
Honestly, the place is just ridden with,

24:57.790 --> 24:59.590
it's just like a Hoarders Anonymous.

25:00.720 --> 25:02.850
- Obviously, I needed a
place to put my clothes,

25:02.850 --> 25:05.180
and so that was where I put them.

25:05.180 --> 25:07.500
- You can't just hyphen off a wardrobe

25:07.500 --> 25:09.500
'cause it's full of your crap.

25:09.500 --> 25:11.040
You can't.
- Like I said,

25:11.040 --> 25:12.213
it's just a storage area.

25:12.213 --> 25:13.130
- No, but it's not a storage area,

25:13.130 --> 25:14.700
just like your fridge downstairs.

25:14.700 --> 25:18.080
This place is plagued
with junk on top of junk.

25:18.080 --> 25:20.680
Freezers overbearing, overfull.

25:20.680 --> 25:21.850
And as for the disgusting way

25:21.850 --> 25:25.040
that the fridge is kept
with the mouldy salad,

25:25.040 --> 25:26.490
there's salad that's festered,

25:26.490 --> 25:30.760
and it's almost sort of
disintegrated in the centre, rotten.

25:30.760 --> 25:32.500
Can I just quickly go on
to the size of the menu?

25:32.500 --> 25:33.333
- It's too big.

25:33.333 --> 25:34.830
- The kitchen's about
as big as my wardrobe.

25:34.830 --> 25:35.663
- It's too, it's way too much.

25:35.663 --> 25:37.220
- But why are you telling me that

25:37.220 --> 25:38.213
when the owner's standing next to you?

25:38.213 --> 25:41.240
- I told her that, but we have told her.

25:41.240 --> 25:42.090
She won't listen.

25:43.520 --> 25:45.240
- Mac and cheese all separated.

25:45.240 --> 25:46.520
Every mouthful is full of grease,

25:46.520 --> 25:49.070
'cause it was slow-cooked
in the microwave.

25:49.070 --> 25:50.980
- And that's the way we do it.

25:50.980 --> 25:53.480
People say that we've
got the best food in town

25:53.480 --> 25:54.639
and the freshest.

25:54.639 --> 25:56.140
- Oh, stop there.

25:56.140 --> 25:58.140
Now you're sounding slightly bizarre.

25:58.140 --> 25:59.503
The best food in town?

26:01.390 --> 26:02.690
Are you okay?

26:02.690 --> 26:04.220
- Well, it depends on how you define okay.

26:04.220 --> 26:05.640
I'm okay by-
- You sure?

26:05.640 --> 26:06.950
- By my standards.

26:06.950 --> 26:08.850
- But mac and cheese? I mean, come on.

26:10.550 --> 26:12.500
You know, what are you looking for now?

26:12.500 --> 26:14.460
Are you taking notes?
- My pen, yeah.

26:14.460 --> 26:15.510
- You're taking notes?

26:15.510 --> 26:17.433
- Yeah, you're making some good points.

26:20.450 --> 26:22.210
- And you're laughing.

26:22.210 --> 26:23.290
What's so funny then?

26:23.290 --> 26:24.563
Help me to understand.

26:25.930 --> 26:28.410
- I don't have anything
to do with the food.

26:28.410 --> 26:30.330
- So I don't know what you're doing.

26:30.330 --> 26:32.540
I've got no idea what you're doing.

26:32.540 --> 26:34.530
- What I ask her to, basically.

26:34.530 --> 26:36.490
- So she does what you say?

26:36.490 --> 26:37.723
- She helps me, yeah.

26:39.510 --> 26:41.400
- Jeff, is this correct?

26:41.400 --> 26:42.790
- I tell them to do one thing,

26:42.790 --> 26:43.750
Ms. Sarah tell them to do another.

26:43.750 --> 26:45.610
- Ms. Sarah tells you
what to do? She just-

26:45.610 --> 26:47.510
- And-
- She says she's a volunteer.

26:47.510 --> 26:51.193
- She tells my crew what
to do, and it piss me off.

26:52.080 --> 26:54.664
I get mad then they blame it on me, so-

26:54.664 --> 26:56.880
- But she's got no authority to do that.

26:56.880 --> 26:59.440
- Jeff, you've never
talked to me about this.

26:59.440 --> 27:00.900
- I have told you-
- Wait a minute.

27:00.900 --> 27:03.670
- I have told you about this.

27:03.670 --> 27:05.110
- Is this true?

27:05.110 --> 27:06.320
Is this the way you treat the staff?

27:06.320 --> 27:07.820
Nothing more humiliating to the team

27:07.820 --> 27:10.160
that are on the ground
keeping this place open

27:10.160 --> 27:12.800
and then a stranger comes in
and tells them what to do.

27:12.800 --> 27:13.810
- Well, she's not a stranger.

27:13.810 --> 27:14.643
She's been coming here since--

27:14.643 --> 27:15.476
- To them she is,

27:15.476 --> 27:18.120
because she's not exactly
qualified to run this place.

27:19.159 --> 27:22.050
This is so screwed up, this is bizarre.

27:22.050 --> 27:23.980
- Ain't nobody hearing me what I'm saying.

27:23.980 --> 27:25.480
- And what kind of
message are you sending?

27:25.480 --> 27:26.980
- The menu need to be down.

27:26.980 --> 27:30.340
- A menu like this, there
must be 50 items on there,

27:30.340 --> 27:34.113
which 49 of them are tapped
out of the bloody freezer.

27:35.070 --> 27:37.590
This place is so messed up.

27:37.590 --> 27:41.292
It's a mess, a disgusting, festering mess.

27:41.292 --> 27:43.207
- Oh, you ain't seen nothing yet.

27:43.207 --> 27:45.707
(tense music)

27:48.760 --> 27:50.497
- Unbelievable.

27:50.497 --> 27:53.576
- I don't know, I'm just
so fucking embarrassed.

27:53.576 --> 27:56.159
- I know, I know. Jeff, I know.

28:09.830 --> 28:13.040
- So far, I've learned that not
only does Karan hoard items,

28:13.040 --> 28:15.410
but she's also a controlling owner.

28:15.410 --> 28:18.430
Tonight, I want to see how
the Town's Inn operates

28:18.430 --> 28:19.570
during the evening.

28:19.570 --> 28:20.820
How are you?
- Good.

28:20.820 --> 28:22.930
- And your name is?
- My name's Tyler.

28:22.930 --> 28:24.500
- Tyler, what do you do?

28:24.500 --> 28:25.360
- Um, I'm a server.

28:25.360 --> 28:26.800
- Okay, great, Tyler and--hello.

28:26.800 --> 28:27.633
- Hi, I'm Gauge.

28:27.633 --> 28:29.520
- Gauge. What do you two do out here?

28:29.520 --> 28:30.830
- We are both servers.

28:30.830 --> 28:31.980
- Come here, so I can talk to you.

28:31.980 --> 28:33.140
Where is the best place to hang this?

28:33.140 --> 28:34.730
- I can hang it for you, sir.

28:34.730 --> 28:37.020
I mean, if we didn't have these
filthy hats laying around--

28:37.020 --> 28:38.970
- I know, why do you have
filthy hats in the hallway?

28:38.970 --> 28:39.820
- Looks like a-
- So-

28:39.820 --> 28:41.090
- Looks like a thrift shop, sir.

28:41.090 --> 28:42.210
- Thrift shop.

28:42.210 --> 28:43.100
How old are you guys?

28:43.100 --> 28:44.219
- I am 17.
- I am also 17.

28:44.219 --> 28:45.470
- 17.

28:45.470 --> 28:47.310
Objectively, what's wrong with this place?

28:47.310 --> 28:50.150
- Well, I think that
we're not well-organized.

28:50.150 --> 28:52.880
I also think that we need
to work on cleanliness.

28:52.880 --> 28:53.713
- Cleanliness.
- Yes.

28:53.713 --> 28:54.630
- Wow, is it that bad?

28:54.630 --> 28:55.730
- It can be.

28:55.730 --> 28:57.060
- So what do you think's dirty?

28:57.060 --> 29:00.210
- Well, honestly, probably the kitchen

29:00.210 --> 29:01.220
and some of the rooms.

29:01.220 --> 29:03.360
- Why you going under
the mat like that, what?

29:03.360 --> 29:05.050
- You asked what was dirty, so I mean,

29:05.050 --> 29:07.160
common things that we
try to clean every day

29:07.160 --> 29:08.840
that we can't always keep an eye on.

29:08.840 --> 29:10.080
- Show me where the
kitchen is please, yeah?

29:10.080 --> 29:11.283
- Okay.
- Thank you.

29:13.040 --> 29:14.190
What happened here?

29:14.190 --> 29:15.467
- Sarah likes to paint on the walls.

29:15.467 --> 29:16.650
- Hello.
- Hello.

29:16.650 --> 29:17.483
- Hi.

29:17.483 --> 29:18.410
- What's this mess here?

29:18.410 --> 29:21.633
- This is a painting, and I--
- A what?

29:22.630 --> 29:23.560
A painting?
- Yes, sir.

29:23.560 --> 29:24.952
- It looks like someone
shat all over the walls.

29:24.952 --> 29:26.440
(Gauge laughing)
- Is that hygienic?

29:26.440 --> 29:27.940
You're painting the walls of the kitchen.

29:27.940 --> 29:29.367
- I have no idea, I thought it was.

29:29.367 --> 29:31.300
- You have no idea so why did you do it?

29:31.300 --> 29:33.850
- The Town's Inn became
Sarah's Town's Inn,

29:33.850 --> 29:35.540
even though she had nothing to do

29:35.540 --> 29:37.330
with owning the establishment.

29:37.330 --> 29:39.110
- Karan, did you see
the mess in the kitchen?

29:39.110 --> 29:40.820
She's painted the wall.

29:40.820 --> 29:42.617
Let me show you something.
- Oh, in here?

29:42.617 --> 29:44.140
- Yeah.
- Yeah, yeah.

29:44.140 --> 29:45.040
- Have you seen it?

29:45.040 --> 29:47.756
- Yes. It's one of my favourite things.

29:47.756 --> 29:48.589
You don't like it?

29:48.589 --> 29:50.160
- It's one of your favourite things?

29:50.160 --> 29:50.993
No, seriously.

29:52.630 --> 29:54.840
- I'm alive, maybe not well.

29:54.840 --> 29:56.619
Did you see the mural in the dining room?

29:56.619 --> 29:57.452
- What?

29:57.452 --> 29:59.880
- That is a children assist-- inn guests.

29:59.880 --> 30:01.260
- That's unique, isn't it?

30:01.260 --> 30:02.170
- What is that?

30:02.170 --> 30:04.870
- Well, it started as a crack in the wall,

30:04.870 --> 30:07.144
and I asked Sarah to make a vine.

30:07.144 --> 30:08.678
- Is there anywhere else you painted?

30:08.678 --> 30:09.980
- There is a, uh--
- Oh, in your room.

30:09.980 --> 30:10.930
- In my room?

30:10.930 --> 30:11.983
Show me, please.

30:15.299 --> 30:17.407
What have you done to my wall?

30:17.407 --> 30:19.560
This is so weird, you paint over cracks.

30:19.560 --> 30:21.050
- I know.
- Look at this here.

30:21.050 --> 30:24.270
- I know, and this,
apparently is something new

30:24.270 --> 30:26.530
that's falling apart. Wow.

30:26.530 --> 30:28.621
- I mean-
- Must be wet.

30:28.621 --> 30:29.463
- Wet, it's soaking wet.

30:29.463 --> 30:34.463
The plaster's just-
- Whoa! (giggling)

30:36.010 --> 30:37.050
- These are bits of card.

30:37.050 --> 30:39.410
- That's correct, it was a temporary fix.

30:39.410 --> 30:41.650
- So it's not a mural,
it's business cards.

30:41.650 --> 30:42.930
you put your cards on here,

30:42.930 --> 30:44.630
and then you paint over the cards?

30:48.370 --> 30:49.937
You should make a label for this:

30:49.937 --> 30:52.820
"Decaying Wall, do not paint over it."

30:52.820 --> 30:57.780
I mean, what, the wall's rotten,

30:57.780 --> 30:59.360
and you just go paint over it?

30:59.360 --> 31:01.110
- It was meant as a temporary fix.

31:01.110 --> 31:02.957
- The wall is rotten.
- You're right.

31:02.957 --> 31:04.450
- And you just paint over it?

31:04.450 --> 31:08.130
You can't just go filling
cracks with tacky painting.

31:08.130 --> 31:09.200
Look at down here!

31:09.200 --> 31:11.513
You've gone over cracks and holes. Look!

31:13.100 --> 31:13.933
Jesus, ugh.

31:16.760 --> 31:18.050
What's that in there?

31:18.050 --> 31:22.650
- Um, I put some sort of a
mesh, because it was a hole

31:22.650 --> 31:26.030
and I didn't want anything
to come through it.

31:26.030 --> 31:27.270
- Jesus.

31:27.270 --> 31:28.810
- I wish you wouldn't use that word.

31:28.810 --> 31:30.580
- What, hole?

31:30.580 --> 31:32.400
Do you want me to sing fucking hallelujah?

31:32.400 --> 31:33.350
- That'd be better.

31:34.536 --> 31:37.590
- Pfff! (coughing)

31:37.590 --> 31:38.480
Can you get me Karan?

31:38.480 --> 31:41.530
- I can get you Karan.
- Please? Jesus.

31:41.530 --> 31:43.213
- Watch your language, sir.

31:47.162 --> 31:48.745
- What in the fuck?

31:50.040 --> 31:51.611
Ms. Karan-
- (gasps) Oh, my goodness.

31:51.611 --> 31:53.320
- Yeah, well, the whole thing
just started coming off.

31:53.320 --> 31:56.560
The wall needs repairing, and
she's just painting over it.

31:56.560 --> 31:59.570
And then secondly, she
found a big hole here,

31:59.570 --> 32:01.710
started putting her cards on there,

32:01.710 --> 32:03.040
and then painted over that.

32:03.040 --> 32:03.873
- Mm-hmm.

32:03.873 --> 32:07.063
- But inside the hole, oh Jesus.

32:09.640 --> 32:10.990
This is not a papier-mache.

32:13.430 --> 32:15.690
What is she doing to your hotel?

32:15.690 --> 32:16.613
- It didn't go outside, I mean,

32:16.613 --> 32:18.920
It's not a hole to the outside.

32:18.920 --> 32:20.520
- It's not a hole to the outside?

32:20.520 --> 32:21.377
- No.
- What does that mean?

32:21.377 --> 32:23.180
- The stone wall is out there.

32:23.180 --> 32:24.239
- But we're sleeping on the inside,

32:24.239 --> 32:25.760
we're not sleeping on the outside.

32:25.760 --> 32:28.100
- Right, so you're not
getting any cold draughts

32:28.100 --> 32:29.140
or anything through there.

32:29.140 --> 32:31.237
- So it's just like I don't
get to use the wardrobe,

32:31.237 --> 32:33.080
and the hole's in the
inside, not the outside,

32:33.080 --> 32:34.770
and we can just do what we want?

32:34.770 --> 32:36.950
- Well, it's solid.
- She's stuffing in--

32:36.950 --> 32:37.783
- It's really solid.

32:37.783 --> 32:39.620
- It needs re-plastering.
- And it's stone out there.

32:39.620 --> 32:41.740
- You can't just paint over that.

32:41.740 --> 32:43.040
- Well, you can.

32:43.040 --> 32:43.873
We did, but.

32:43.873 --> 32:46.433
- And then stick Brillo pads in the hole.

32:47.760 --> 32:49.630
You can't just Band-Aid this place.

32:49.630 --> 32:51.020
Oh, my good God.

32:51.020 --> 32:53.430
Just wash my hands.

32:53.430 --> 32:55.310
- An order of French bread as an app.

32:55.310 --> 32:56.570
- All right.

32:56.570 --> 32:59.050
- Um, what is that there, a sports bar?

32:59.050 --> 33:00.680
Are these TV screens, what are those?

33:00.680 --> 33:02.430
- Microwaves.
- Microwaves.

33:02.430 --> 33:03.690
- How many microwaves have you got?

33:03.690 --> 33:06.983
- Well, there's four here,
and one in there, that's five.

33:06.983 --> 33:09.580
- Five microwaves and two chefs?

33:09.580 --> 33:11.320
- Two chefs.

33:11.320 --> 33:12.153
- Oh, my God.

33:12.996 --> 33:15.540
Everywhere I turn, there's
just junk everywhere.

33:15.540 --> 33:17.150
Well, this is cooking stuff.

33:17.150 --> 33:18.487
- Trust me, I know what cooking stuff is.

33:18.487 --> 33:19.320
This is not cooking stuff.

33:19.320 --> 33:20.170
- Okay.

33:20.170 --> 33:23.200
- How does this kitchen
function, give me a little tour.

33:23.200 --> 33:24.033
- Very challenging.

33:24.033 --> 33:25.440
- It's very, very challenging.

33:25.440 --> 33:26.273
- What's that in there?

33:26.273 --> 33:29.415
- That's a burger that I'm heating up.

33:29.415 --> 33:31.460
- A boiled-
- Yep.

33:31.460 --> 33:32.870
- You're boiling a burger.

33:32.870 --> 33:34.063
- I'm just heating it back up.

33:34.063 --> 33:35.400
- When you say heating it back up,

33:35.400 --> 33:36.890
why aren't you cooking it from fresh?

33:36.890 --> 33:38.300
- 'Cause we make them ahead of time.

33:38.300 --> 33:40.160
- This is what we got here, we don't.

33:40.160 --> 33:42.171
- A boiled burger!

33:42.171 --> 33:43.960
Are you aware the burgers are boiled?

33:43.960 --> 33:45.570
- Um, no.

33:45.570 --> 33:48.030
- Do you think a customer
would want a burger

33:48.030 --> 33:49.370
boiled in water?

33:49.370 --> 33:50.690
- They seem to like them.

33:50.690 --> 33:52.000
- Just taste the water.

33:52.000 --> 33:53.405
- Do I have to?

33:53.405 --> 33:54.940
- Funny, you won't taste it.

33:54.940 --> 33:56.350
- Okay, well, I just...

33:59.650 --> 34:01.920
Tastes like water with beef in it.

34:01.920 --> 34:03.670
- That seems okay?

34:03.670 --> 34:06.010
- When they fix it up
on a nice Kaiser roll

34:06.010 --> 34:07.527
